2.10 Concluding remarks
The âdisplacementâ approach to the analysis of elastic solids is still undoubtedly the most popular and easily understood procedure. In many of the following chapters we shall use the general formulae developed here in the context of linear elastic analysis (e.g., in Chapter 6). These are also applicable in the context of non-linear analysis, the main variants being the deï¬nitions of the stresses, generalized strains, and other associated quantities.7 In Chapter 3 we shall show that the procedures developed here are but a particular case of ï¬nite element discretization applied to the governing differential equations written in terms of displacements.31 Clearly, alternative starting points are possible. Some of these will be mentioned in Chapters 10 and 11.

