with Î» now being an unknown function deï¬ned only on . Alternatively, if the constraint C is applicable only at one or more points of the system, then the simple addition of Î»T C(u) at these points to the general functional will introduce a discrete number of constraints. It appears, therefore, possible to always introduce additional functions Î» and modify a functional to include any prescribed constraints. In the âdiscretizationâ process we shall now have to use trial functions to describe both u and Î». Writing, for instance, Ë u=
